R IGHT TO COUNSEL The Sixth Amendment to the United States Constitution states that i n all criminal prosecutions, the accused shall enjoy the right to . . . have the assistance of counsel for his defens e. R IGHT TO COUNSEL The Sixth Amendment to the United States Constitution states that i n all criminal prosecutions, the accused shall enjoy the right to . . . have the assistance of counsel for his defens e. The right to counsel is a fundamental right, and thus , it imposes an obligatory duty on to the states to provide counsel to indigent defendants through the Fourteenth Amendment. Gideon v. Wainwright , 372 U.S. 335, 342- 44, 83 S. Ct. 792, 9 L. Ed. 2d 799 1963 Luis v. United States
